Deliberately inconsistent DOM: the `.toggle` is checked but the `<li>` has no
`completed` class. `[x]` reads the checkbox, `~…~` reads the class, and they are
independent, so this projects `[x] buy milk` — the box, no strike marks. A real
app would never render this, but a buggy one could, and the projection must show
exactly one of the two markers.
Pins: `[x]` and `~…~` are independent outputs.

This fixture omits the footer to keep the case on the item line; each region
projects on its own marker, so a shown main with no footer is a valid input.

-- dom.html --
<section class="todoapp">
	<header class="header">
		<h1>todos</h1>
		<input class="new-todo" placeholder="What needs to be done?">
	</header>
	<section class="main">
		<input id="toggle-all" class="toggle-all" type="checkbox">
		<label for="toggle-all">Mark all as complete</label>
		<ul class="todo-list">
			<li data-id="t1">
				<div class="view">
					<input class="toggle" type="checkbox" checked>
					<label>buy milk</label>
					<button class="destroy"></button>
				</div>
				<input class="edit" value="buy milk">
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</section>

-- projection.txt --
v > ""
#t1 [x] buy milk
